'''Arch L. Madsen''' (December 4, 1913 â€“ April 7, 1997) was the founder of [[Bonneville International]] and a president of KSL.<ref name="meridian mag">{{cite web|title=The Battlefield of the Mind: A Conversation with Arch L. Madsen |url=http://ldsmag.com/ldsmag/ideas/090213mind.html |work=Meridian Magazine |accessdate=7 May 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508030627/http://ldsmag.com/ldsmag/ideas/090213mind.html |archivedate=8 May 2014 }}</ref> He was a recipient of the [[Peabody Award]], the Distinguished Service Award from the [[National Association of Broadcasters]], and the "Giant in Our City" award from the [[Salt Lake Area Chamber of Commerce]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deseretnews.com/article/553903/Arch-L-Madsen.html?pg%3Dall|title=Arch L. Madsen|date=April 9, 1997|website=deseretnews.com |publisher=Deseret News |accessdate=May 4, 2014}}</ref>

